original: Ivarson, Karl-Erik, tandläkare, Huskvarna, f. 28/6/11 i Huskvarna av Ivar Johansson o. Martha Viktoria Pettersson. G. 38 m. Gunvor Strömberg. Barn: Hans f. 41, Lars 43. — Studiex. i Jönköp. 31, farm. stud. 32, tand-l:kand. 34, tandl. 36. Assist, i Gisla-ved 36, prakt, i Huskvarna sed. 37, skoltandl. v. Huskvarna samrealsk. sed. 38. Ordf. i Sv:es tandl :förb. studentsektion 35-36, v. ordf. i Jönköp. 1. tandl :fören.
translated: Ivarson, Karl-Erik, dentist, Huskvarna, born on June 28, 1911 in Huskvarna to Ivar Johansson and Martha Viktoria Pettersson. Married in 1938 to Gunvor Strömberg. Children: Hans born in 1941, Lars in 1943. Karl-Erik completed his high school education in Jönköping in 1931, studied pharmacy in 1932, completed his dental studies in 1934 and became a licensed dentist in 1936. He worked as an assistant in Gislaved in 1936, and began his own dental practice in Huskvarna in 1937 and became a school dentist at Huskvarna Samrealskolan in 1938. He was Chairman of the Swedish Dental Association student section from 1935-1936, and Vice Chairman of the Jönköping 1st Dental Association.
